<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4283906>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "FIGURE 5. Duplominona trimera n. sp. (A) Habitus of a living animal; see Fig. 2 A for interpretation of anatomical features. (B) Reconstruction of the cirrus. (C) Reconstruction of the genital areas from sagittal sections. (D, E) Morphology of distal (D) and proximal (E) spines. (F, G) Micrographs of the caudal part of living animals. (H) Micrograph of a metaphasic plate (I–K) Micrographs of cirri and accessory organ (I). (L, M) Micrographs of sagittal sections of the bursa-vagina system (L) and copulatory and accessory organs (M). (Scale bars: B, D, E, I –M = 10 μm; F, G = 50 μm; I = 5 μm)." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4283906/files/figure.png" .
